{
  "workflow_id": "architecture",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Blueprint-to-architecture design with internal modes. mode_resolver picks the mode (design / stack / update / review / reconcile / materialize) and routes to a task graph; all six modes are implemented. design and stack build from a blueprint; review / update / reconcile operate on an existing architecture and share an artifact resolver; materialize consolidates accepted update notes into one canonical architecture document. design tasks: resolve blueprint input → detect existing architecture → prepare context → parse (incl. blueprint §9 Product Experience Direction + §19 Recommended Next Stages) → traceability map → clarify → solution strategy → goals/constraints → provisional tech stack (+ provisional tech assumptions + tech-stack selection handoff) → traditional-vs-AI boundary → skill/MCP decision → tech-stack/boundary coherence → C4 views → interface contracts → data contracts → security/trust boundaries → observability/audit → failure handling → testing/evaluation → ADRs → rule-pack review → draft (incl. Experience Architecture + Recommended Next Stages and Downstream Handoffs) → quality-gate self-check → final document. stack_tasks: resolve stack inputs → technology decision drivers → stack selection → architecture impact + update verdict → stack quality gate → final stack document (<topic-slug>-architecture-tech-stack.md). materialize_tasks: discover and order accepted inputs → apply patches + detect conflicts → final canonical documents (<topic-slug>-architecture-design.vX.Y.Z.md + artifact registry + open-question ledger). Pure-LLM transformation: every task is a reasoning step driven by a prompt file; there is no deterministic CLI/MCP backend. The manifest is valid as documentation for a prompt-driven agent and ready for a future runtime runner; if no runner exists, follow the task order manually. v0.2.0–v0.8.0: see prior description for quality, hardening, mode-split, remaining-modes, and cross-skill-artifact-contract passes. v1.0.0 cross-section-consistency pass: design mode adds a Cross-Section Consistency Pass (prompt 22c) that checks five invariants — §23 MVP operations present in §12 interface contracts, §23.3/§23.4 user-visible states mapped to §14, §23.6 human-review actions having §12 contract + §14 transition + §16 audit event + §18 failure behaviour, §23.4 progress items with §16 observability events, and §24 handoff tables referencing only formalized or deferred operations — logging any gap in §25 and §27. The quality-gate prompt (23) adds five v0.9.0 cross-section consistency gates (gates 20–24) and updates the instructions to emit them in the §26 table. The architecture design template (§26) gains a Cross-Section Consistency Gate sub-table. The SKILL.md gains gate 29. v0.9.0 materialize pass: adds materialize mode (materialize_tasks: materialize_02_discover_and_order → materialize_03_apply_patches → materialize_04_final_document). Materialize discovers the base architecture and all accepted update notes by topic slug, validates acceptance criteria, orders by version/update history, checks six conflict classes (SECTION_CONFLICT / PATCH_TARGET_MISSING / TEXT_ANCHOR_GONE / CONTRACT_CONFLICT / SUPERSESSION_CONFLICT / BREAKING_CHANGE_UNRESOLVED — all BLOCKING), applies accepted patches section-by-section without inventing new decisions, removes resolved provisional wording, updates ADRs/open questions/handoffs, and produces a 30-section canonical architecture (27 original + Applied Updates + Superseded Patch Notes + Implementation-Plan Readiness) plus an artifact registry and an open-question ledger. Stops on any BLOCKING conflict and writes a materialization-blocked report. Also v0.9.0: update mode grows from 11 to 13 sections — adds §5 Patch Manifest (machine-readable YAML with update-type taxonomy: NONE / NOTE_ONLY / ADR_ONLY / CONTRACT_PATCH / SECURITY_PATCH / OBSERVABILITY_PATCH / STRUCTURAL_PATCH / BREAKING_CHANGE) and §12 Feedback Closure Matrix (tracking which downstream feedback items are resolved by which patches). Skill version metadata must use UNKNOWN — resolver could not determine this value instead of bare unknown; quality gate warns on any UNKNOWN field.",
  "mandatory_gates": [
    "rule_pack_review",
    "quality_gate_self_check",
    "final_architecture_document"
  ],
  "tasks": [
